DeltaNet layer — inference — one token

Input: x (hidden state), X (residual accumulator)
Constants: D (hidden dimension), w (learned weight vector per norm — one scalar per element of the hidden state, learned during training, stored in the model weights)


PRIMITIVES
==========

Dimensional notation: number of repeated symbols = loop depth.
Scalar = one instruction. Every extra symbol = one more nested loop.

  *           scalar multiply — one FMUL
  **          vector multiply — loop of FMULs (elementwise)
  ***         matrix multiply — loop of loop of FMULs (outer product)
  ****        tensor multiply — loop of loop of loop of FMULs

  +           scalar add — one FADD
  ++          vector add — loop of FADDs (elementwise)
  +++         matrix add — loop of loop of FADDs

  -           scalar subtract
  --          vector subtract (elementwise)

  /           scalar divide
  //          vector divide (elementwise)

  Σ           reduction — collapse one dimension (shuffle tree) — O(log N), NOT a loop

  exp         e^x  (scalar; wrap in ** to apply elementwise)
  log         ln(x) (scalar; wrap in ** to apply elementwise)
  1/          reciprocal (scalar; wrap in ** to apply elementwise)
  1/√         reciprocal square root (scalar; wrap in ** to apply elementwise)
  √           square root (scalar; wrap in ** to apply elementwise)

  project     W4A16 dequant GEMV — effectively ****Σ with dequant
  matvec      FP32 state GEMV — effectively ***Σ

`outer` is gone. It is ***.


COMPOSITES
==========

These are not primitives. They are names for sequences of primitives.

  sigmoid   = * -1, exp, ++, //
  silu      = * -1, exp, ++, //, **
  softplus  = exp, ++, log
  normalise = **, Σ, / D, 1/√, ** w
  l2norm    = **, Σ, 1/√, **

  project (W4A16 GPTQ):
    for each output element:
      for each group of 8 packed weights:
        load packed u32           (8 weights in 32 bits)
        load scale                (one per group of 128 weights)
        8x: extract nibble        (shift, mask)
            - integer to float
            - subtract zero point  (- 8)
            - * scale
            - * input element
            + accumulate
      Σ across threads            (sum partial products)


FULL DECOMPOSITION — 66 STEPS
==============================

RMSNorm on input hidden state

 1  **               square each element
 2  Σ                sum all squares
 3  / D              mean of squares
 4  √                root mean square
 5  //               x / rms (elementwise)
 6  ** w             scale by learned weight (elementwise)

 7  project          Q projection
 8  project          K projection
 9  project          V projection

L2-norm on K (after projection, before delta-update)

10  **               square each element of K
11  Σ                sum all squares
12  √                √(sum)
13  //               K / sqrt(sum)    =  L2-norm(K)

SiLU on Q

14  * -1             -Q
15  exp              e^(-Q)
16  ++               1 + e^(-Q)  (elementwise add scalar)
17  //               1 / (1 + e^(-Q))  =  sigmoid(Q)  (elementwise reciprocal)
18  **               Q * sigmoid(Q)    =  SiLU(Q)  (elementwise multiply)

L2-norm on Q (after SiLU, before matvec)

19  **               square each element of Q
20  Σ                sum all squares
21  √                √(sum)
22  //               Q / sqrt(sum)    =  L2-norm(Q)

Sigmoid on beta

23  * -1             -beta
24  exp              e^(-beta)
25  ++               1 + e^(-beta)
26  //               1 / (1 + e^(-beta))  =  sigmoid(beta)

Decay gate (GatedDeltaNet)
  a_proj = in_proj_a @ x  (already computed as part of in_proj)
  g = -exp(A_log) * softplus(a_proj + dt_bias)
  decay = exp(g)

27  ++               t = a_proj + dt_bias  (elementwise add)
28  exp              exp(t)
29  ++               1 + exp(t)
30  log              log(1 + exp(t))      =  softplus(t)
31  exp              exp(A_log)
32  * -1             -exp(A_log)
33  **               g = -exp(A_log) * softplus(t)  (elementwise multiply)
34  exp              decay = exp(g)

Delta rule (with decay)

  State update decomposes to:
    recall     = matvec      S @ K  (FP32 GEMV — ***Σ)
    correction = --          V - recall  (elementwise subtract)
    correction = **          beta * correction  (elementwise multiply)
    update_mat = ***         correction ⊗ K  (outer product — loop of loop of FMULs)
    decay_S    = **          decay * S  (elementwise multiply)
    S'         = +++         decay_S + update_mat  (matrix add — loop of loop of FADDs)
    output     = matvec      S' @ Q  (FP32 GEMV — ***Σ)

35  matvec           recall = S @ K
36  --               correction_v = V - recall  (elementwise)
37  **               correction = beta * correction_v  (elementwise)
38  ***              update_mat = correction ⊗ K  (outer product)
39  **               decay_S = decay * S  (elementwise)
40  +++              S = decay_S + update_mat  (matrix add)
41  matvec           output = S @ Q

Output gate (g_proj)

42  project          z = W_z @ x  (output gate projection)
43  * -1             -z
44  exp              e^(-z)
45  ++               1 + e^(-z)
46  //               1 / (1 + e^(-z))  =  sigmoid(z)
47  **               output * sigmoid(z)  (gate multiply, elementwise)

RMSNorm on gated output

48  **               square each element
49  Σ                sum all squares
50  / D              mean of squares
51  √                root mean square
52  //               output / rms  (elementwise)
53  ** w             scale by learned weight (elementwise)

54  project          output projection
55  ++               residual into X  (elementwise add)

RMSNorm on X (MLP input)

56  **               square each element
57  Σ                sum all squares
58  / D              mean of squares
59  √                root mean square
60  //               X / rms  (elementwise)
61  ** w             scale by learned weight (elementwise)

62  project          gate projection
63  project          up projection

SiLU on gate

64  * -1             -gate
65  exp              e^(-gate)
66  ++               1 + e^(-gate)
67  //               1 / (1 + e^(-gate))  =  sigmoid(gate)
68  **               gate * sigmoid(gate) =  SiLU(gate)  (elementwise)

69  **               gate * up  (elementwise multiply)

70  project          down projection
71  ++               residual into X  (elementwise add)
